          <text x="545" y="170" text-anchor="middle" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Day 14</text>
          <text x="545" y="185" text-anchor="middle" fill="#71717a" font-size="9">Photo Request</text>

          <circle cx="650" cy="130" r="18" fill="#ec4899" opacity="0.3"/>
          <circle cx="650" cy="130" r="10" fill="#ec4899"/>
          <text x="650" y="170" text-anchor="middle" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Day 21</text>
          <text x="650" y="185" text-anchor="middle" fill="#71717a" font-size="9">Review Request</text>

          <!-- Arrow heads -->
          <polygon points="648,120 660,130 648,140" fill="#374151"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p>A complete aftercare automation sequence covers the full healing journey. Here's the proven cadence:</p>

      <h3>Day 1: Aftercare Instructions</h3>
      <h4>What to Include</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Washing instructions (how often, what soap to use)</li>
        <li>Moisturizing recommendations</li>
        <li>What's normal vs. what requires a call</li>
        <li>Products to avoid (sun, swimming, gym for 2 weeks)</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Best Practice</h4>
      <p>Link to a full aftercare page on your website. Clients who read written instructions have 60% fewer follow-up questions.</p>
      <h5>Sample SMS</h5>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #ccc;">"Hey [Name]! Thanks for your session today. Here's what to expect tonight: [link]. Any urgent questions? — [Studio]"</p>

      <h3>Day 3: Healing Check-In</h3>
      <h4>Medical vs. Relationship Objective</h4>
      <p>This message serves two purposes simultaneously. From a medical standpoint, it catches early warning signs (infection, allergic reaction). From a relationship standpoint, it shows genuine care.</p>
      <h5>Sample SMS</h5>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #ccc;">"Hi [Name], just checking in on your tattoo from [Date]! How's the healing going? Any questions? — [Artist]"</p>

      <h3>Day 7: Progress Check + Touch-Up</h3>
      <h4>Why This Matters</h4>
      <p>Day 7 is when tattoos are peeling and clients worry. Reassurance at this stage prevents panic calls.</p>
      <h5>Touch-Up Booking Strategy</h5>
      <p>Most clients forget to book touch-ups. This reminder increases touch-up bookings by 50%. Make it easy: include a direct booking link.</p>

      <h3>Day 14: Healed Photo Request</h3>
      <h4>Submission Rate by Method</h4>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead><tr class="border-b border-ink-700"><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Method</th><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Submission Rate</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Manual DM</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">10-15%</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Automated SMS</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">35-45%</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Auto SMS + incentive (10% off)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">55-65%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Auto email with upload link</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">40-50%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Day 21: Review Request + Referral Prompt</h3>
      <p>At three weeks, clients are healed and happy — the optimal time to ask for a review. Studies show that Google reviews requested within this window are 2x more likely to be completed.</p>

      <!-- ============================================================ -->
