      <!-- H2: IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE                                       -->
      <!-- ============================================================ -->
      <h2>Implementation Guide: 4-Step Setup</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Define Your Sequence</h3>
      <p>Map out your ideal aftercare timeline. Start with the standard 5-message cadence and customize from there.</p>
      <h4>Customization Options</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Timing: Adjust delays per message (e.g., day 5 instead of day 3 for complex pieces)</li>
        <li>Channel: SMS vs email per message type</li>
        <li>Content: Studio voice, specific product recommendations</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step 2: Write Your Templates</h3>
      <h4>SMS Templates</h4>
      <p>Keep SMS under 160 characters for single-message delivery. Use personalization tokens.</p>
      <h5>Day 1 Template</h5>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #ccc;">"Thanks [Name]! Aftercare: wash gently 2x/day, light moisturize, no sun/swim/gym for 2 wks. Questions? [link] — [Artist]"</p>
      <h5>Day 3 Template</h5>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #ccc;">"Hi [Name] — checking on your [body part] tattoo from [date]. All good? Reply with any questions!"</p>
      <h5>Day 14 Template</h5>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #ccc;">"Would love to see how your tattoo healed! Reply with a photo and we'll enter you in our monthly healed-artist feature 🖤"</p>

      <h4>Email Templates</h4>
      <p>Use email for rich content — aftercare PDFs, photo upload portals, review links.</p>
      <h5>Day 14 Email Subject Lines (A/B Test Data)</h5>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead><tr class="border-b border-ink-700"><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Subject Line</th><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Open Rate</th><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Photo Submission</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">"How's your tattoo healing?"</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">28%</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">42%</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">"Show off your healed ink! 🖤"</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">34%</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">51%</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">"[Artist] wants to see your healed tattoo"</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">41%</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">55%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">"Your healed photo = 10% off next booking"</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">47%</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">63%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Step 3: Connect to Booking</h3>
      <p>The trigger must be automatic. Manual trigger defeats the purpose. Ensure your chosen platform integrates with your booking system so aftercare launches without any human action.</p>

      <h3>Step 4: Monitor and Optimize</h3>
      <h4>Key Metrics to Track</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Delivery rate (target: >98%)</li>
        <li>Open/read rate (target: SMS >90%, email >25%)</li>
        <li>Photo submission rate (target: >40%)</li>
        <li>Review completion rate (target: >15% of requests → review)</li>
        <li>Return booking rate from aftercare recipients</li>
      </ul>
      <h5>Optimization Levers</h5>
      <ul>
        <li>Timing: A/B test day 3 vs day 5 check-in</li>
        <li>Channel: Switch SMS-only clients to email for photo uploads</li>
        <li>Incentives: Test 10% off vs free touch-up vs entry to drawing</li>
        <li>Length: Shorter messages (under 100 words) get 2x more replies</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ============================================================ -->
      <!-- H2: FAQ                                                        -->
      <!-- ============================================================ -->
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>General Questions</h3>
      <h4>Is aftercare automation expensive?</h4>
      <p>No. InkFlow's aftercare automation starts at $9.99/month on the Starter plan, with full automation included in the Pro plan at $29.99/month. Most studios recoup the cost from a single additional booking per month.</p>
      <h4>Do I need technical skills to set it up?</h4>
      <p>No. The setup takes 10 minutes and requires no coding or technical knowledge. You write templates like you'd write a text message.</p>

      <h3>Client Experience Questions</h3>
      <h4>Will clients find automated messages impersonal?</h4>
      <p>Not if they're well-written. The best automated aftercare messages feel personal because they're personalized with the client's name, artist name, and session details. Use a conversational tone, not corporate marketing speak.</p>
      <h4>What if a client replies with a medical concern?</h4>
      <p>The automation handles the check-in. If they reply with a concern, the message goes to your inbox and you take over. The system isn't replacing you — it's ensuring nothing falls through the cracks.</p>

      <h3>Results Questions</h3>
      <h4>How many healed photos can I expect?</h4>
      <p>Studios using automated aftercare collect healed photos from 40-60% of clients, compared to 10-15% with manual follow-up. The key is asking at the right time (day 14) with a simple process.</p>
      <h4>How long until I see results?</h4>
      <p>Most studios see an increase in healed photos within the first week (as day-14 messages fire for recent clients). Review improvements show within 3-4 weeks. Client retention improvements show within 3 months.</p>
